  'GitHub Release Management - Comprehensive release orchestration with AI swarm coordination, versioning, testing, deployment',
  'claude-code',
  'skill',
  '[{"solution": "Create simple GitHub release with auto-generated changelog", "cli": {"macos": "gh release create v2.0.0 --draft --generate-notes --title \"Release v2.0.0\" && npx claude-flow github release-create --version \"2.0.0\" --build-artifacts --deploy-targets \"npm,docker,github\"", "linux": "gh release create v2.0.0 --draft --generate-notes --title \"Release v2.0.0\" && npx claude-flow github release-create --version \"2.0.0\" --build-artifacts --deploy-targets \"npm,docker,github\"", "windows": "gh release create v2.0.0 --draft --generate-notes --title \"Release v2.0.0\" && npx claude-flow github release-create --version \"2.0.0\" --build-artifacts --deploy-targets \"npm,docker,github\""}, "manual": "1. Get previous release tag\n2. Generate changelog from commits\n3. Create draft release\n4. Update package.json version\n5. Create release branch\n6. Create PR and wait for approval\n7. Merge and tag release", "note": "Use --draft flag for review before publishing"}, {"solution": "Execute coordinated multi-agent release with comprehensive testing and validation", "cli": {"macos": "npx claude-flow swarm init --topology hierarchical && npx claude-flow sparc pipeline \"Release v2.0.0 with full validation\" --monitor --output-sqlite", "linux": "npx claude-flow swarm init --topology hierarchical && npx claude-flow sparc pipeline \"Release v2.0.0 with full validation\" --monitor --output-sqlite", "windows": "npx claude-flow swarm init --topology hierarchical && npx claude-flow sparc pipeline \"Release v2.0.0 with full validation\" --monitor --output-sqlite"}, "manual": "1. Initialize release swarm with 6 specialized agents\n2. Run version and breaking change analysis\n3. Generate categorized changelog with migration guides\n4. Execute multi-stage test suite\n5. Build artifacts for all platforms\n6. Create and publish release\n7. Monitor post-release metrics", "note": "Hierarchical topology for structured release coordination"}, {"solution": "Orchestrate multi-package monorepo release with cross-package validation", "cli": {"macos": "npx claude-flow github multi-release --repos \"frontend:v2.0.0,backend:v2.1.0,cli:v1.5.0\" --ensure-compatibility --atomic-release --synchronized --rollback-all-on-failure", "linux": "npx claude-flow github multi-release --repos \"frontend:v2.0.0,backend:v2.1.0,cli:v1.5.0\" --ensure-compatibility --atomic-release --synchronized --rollback-all-on-failure", "windows": "npx claude-flow github multi-release --repos \"frontend:v2.0.0,backend:v2.1.0,cli:v1.5.0\" --ensure-compatibility --atomic-release --synchronized --rollback-all-on-failure"}, "manual": "1. Initialize mesh topology for cross-package coordination\n2. Spawn package-specific agents\n3. Update all package versions and dependencies\n4. Run cross-package compatibility tests\n5. Create unified release PR\n6. Execute coordinated deployment\n7. Validate all packages deployed correctly", "note": "Atomic releases ensure consistency across packages"}, {"solution": "Execute emergency hotfix with fast-track validation and immediate deployment", "cli": {"macos": "npx claude-flow github emergency-release --issue 789 --severity critical --target-version v1.2.4 --cherry-pick-commits --bypass-checks security-only --fast-track --notify-all", "linux": "npx claude-flow github emergency-release --issue 789 --severity critical --target-version v1.2.4 --cherry-pick-commits --bypass-checks security-only --fast-track --notify-all", "windows": "npx claude-flow github emergency-release --issue 789 --severity critical --target-version v1.2.4 --cherry-pick-commits --bypass-checks security-only --fast-track --notify-all"}, "manual": "1. Create hotfix branch from last stable release\n2. Cherry-pick critical bug fixes\n3. Run only critical validation tests\n4. Create emergency release\n5. Immediately publish to registries\n6. Deploy with high priority\n7. Notify all stakeholders", "note": "Security checks still mandatory even in fast-track mode"}]'::jsonb,
